    {
      "id": "68",
      "name": "Lore",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "customize",
          "data": {
            "data": {
              "parsed_content": [
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Fujin",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/03/15/237301566/28d436515e5f0695e04a902ebcc79143_4622881255621272880.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Thousands of years ago, long before the Archon War, there was another goddess in Chenyu Vale, who Fujin and her friend, Herblord, served. Fujin is an illuminated beast, whose true form is a carp, but she herself prefers the human form. One day, she defeated the ancient Suanni, Lingyuan, known as the Mountain Lord. She did not kill the azure Suanni, but became her friend. At first, Fujin, like Lingyuan, did not understand people and did not like them for their excessive demands, passion for hoarding and eternal desire to have more of what they needed. She could not understand why people's sorrows and joys depended on \"wealth.\" But over the years, she accepted people: a child's cry began to break her heart, and an old person's shattered memories began to sadden her. Fujin realized that people were also part of the vale.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/03/15/237301566/618c50edcbf897e21a1daa5ac5a0763f_1811410172888703217.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "For the sake of the people of Chenyu Vale, Fujin performed the Rainjade Rite, ruled the rivers and mountains in the name of her master. The ritual altered the vale's spirit veins and elemental energy so that people could live there. The Rainjade Rite was once a big event where everyone rejoiced in abundance, laughed, danced in animal costumes, and set off fireworks to drive away evil spirits. In those calm days, Fujin climbed the waterfalls of Mt. Aocang and Mt. Hulao, where she met Adepti whose strength and wisdom far eclipsed her.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Once, Fujin planted a tea tree on Lingyuan’s mountain, planning to invite Cloud Retainer and Mountain Shaper for tea.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Seriously? You plant trees any way you like on my turf, and you have the nerve to spout such things?\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/03/15/237301566/1158bb1575081f8ca8dabf6014efed2f_4307364717859963273.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Later, people took branches of this tree and grafted them to the other side of the Bishui River. They began holding tea ceremonies in gratitude to Fujin and worshiped her as an Adeptus. The fragrance of tea would also travel from this place, Chenyu Vale, to Liyue Harbor, and from there to many more places still. One of the legends concerning the tea trees of Chenyu Vale goes like this:",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"No matter the waters, soil, or sunlight, this sort of tree only grows lushly in Chenyu Vale. This is because it remembers the promise that old friends made in the ancient past beside the tea sapling.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/03/15/237301566/0fed1cd78224e2e1c5f6f05aedc15696_8551513999407387991.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Unlike the Adepti of the south, to whom Rex Lapis granted \"illumination\" and the ability to create their own abodes, Fujin does not have such power and considers herself the weakest Adeptus, that's why her chambers are more like a \"cave\" than an abode. She was not able to leave fresh water for too long, nor live in salty waters, so her Adeptal friends gave her a \"teacup,\" inside of which there was a subspace where she could live. The spring within the chalice would never dry up, making it a fine place to temporarily stay. It could hold a reflection of the sun and moon and could play host to swimming fish. Fujin's friends wanted to take her to Guili Plains and Liyue Harbor, to meet those lovely people they spoke of, but that never happened.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
